{
  "stem": "8892.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they open up every drawer and my poor mother just in bed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Then in the end-- and I'm going into the bedroom where she was laying-- in the end, the soldier tells, I think, the Hungarian police, get her out of bed.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he says at first, roughly, he says, get out of bed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my mother says, I can't.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I am very sick.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I just had an operation.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the German will not accept this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he takes the gun, the shotgun, puts it on the bed, lifts up the mattress like-- and literally lifts my mother in the air.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Just she-- she fell off the bed, and she faints.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that point, my father comes in.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I thought my father was going to kill both of them right there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had a Hungarian temper, and by that time he was very strained, and he could hardly hold his temper in all this.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He grew up that he was born and his grandfather and everything is going chaos.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this was the first bad experience that I noticed at the time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, of course, this went on like two weeks, or not even two weeks.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "All I know is there was-- a day after Pesach, OK, which was in April, beginning of April.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then about four days-- all right, so anyway, and then I have to go to trace back this, because I want you to understand how naive we were.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "As the German comes in, and my father sees what's going on, he picks up my sister.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He picks my sister up and pays off our-- because we had Gentiles all around us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It wasn't just Jews, Jews.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Gentiles were very close neighbors and pays him.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
